CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley...Lower left: A well-fitted room. Diners pause to listen to program...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Large group of women and men, including two men in foreground wearing dark suits, seated in wooden folding chairs around banquet tables, in Central Baptist Church for banquet honoring Talley
